12:
What, you want to go for a round
two?
16: Just who the hell... are you?!
21:
Ugh, it's like I'm watching a stupid
kids' show play out.
29: Better quit while you're ahead, pal.
34: Or else I'll make you regret it.
41:
Ryuichi, you can stick around if you
want, but I'm out. See ya.
46:
They were just kids, yeah? What the
heck was that all about? That boy
had some weird powers too...
49:
And you, don't go disappearing on
me again, ya hear?
80:
Nimbus is one of my most trusted
friends!
84:
Huh? Ayumu, what're you going on
about?
89:
I don't know who this Ayumu is
either. I'm... Ugh, my head!
93:
You can't seriously mean that. Why
else would you look exactly like him?
98:
Stella and Light are waiting for us.
We should head over before they
start panicking. We can talk there.
112:
And you're certain he's not just
someone who looks a lot like your
Ayumu?
115:
I mean, his eyes are a different color
now, but... I've been with Ayumu
since middle school.
120:
We weren't friends until high school,
but... I'd know that face anywhere.
He's Ayumu, one hundred percent.
125:
Middle school... High school... Those
are different types of academies,
right?
135:
I recognize the words... but it's
strange.
137:
Instead of feeling like I forgot
something, it's more like... the
memories are carved out from
where they should be. It feels...
wrong somehow.
141:
I'm sorry, Yuki. Shota. I don't know
who either of you are.
145:
Ayumu, there's someone you have
to meet.
148:
I don't know if she'll be the one to jog
your memory, but... it's worth a try, if
you're willing.
152:
That's not a bad idea. We could use
more information about this world.
165: Oh, that's what Zekhel gave us
170:
The heck is that giant hunk of tech?
An antique?
175:
Nova and I are using our powers to
form a connection through this
device.
180:
This time, I'm on the outside as the
anchor. Without me, you'll lose your
tether to our world, so I have to
remain here.
184:
What happens if we get...
untethered?
188:
Time will start to pass differently,
and... well, let's just say I wouldn't
recommend it.
193:
Sounds like you've got an important
job...
197:
I promise I won't disappoint. I'll also
see what I can do about connecting
that place to Starview.
200:
...I never expected you'd actually find
another world so deep in the Rift.
203:
But there's no mistaking the
presence I sense. Leve is there.
212:
It's been one surprise after the next,
but I'm confident you'll be able to
pull through, one way or another.
215: I believe in you, my partner in crime.
225:
Nimbus and I will remain here, as it
seems our appearances might
cause unnecessary concern.
230:
I'll leave one of these devices with
you. Do you know how to use it?
234:
I-I believe so... But a refresher
couldn't hurt.
238:
You better listen as well, Nimbus...
I'm not so good with these types of
things...
242:
I'm having a hard time wrapping my
head around all this.
245:
Eh, it's not like this is THAT crazy,
right? After everything else we've
been through?
249:
What with the earthquake stranding
us here, and people getting powers
left and right... Honestly, it almost
makes sense there're other worlds
out there.
253:
Leave it to Ayumu to make friends in
another world. He really is amazing...
256:
He's always belonged in a class of
his own...
260:
Good at reading the room too,
unlike me.
263:
It was weird hearing him say our
names like he didn't know us
though. Guess he actually doesn't
remember us...
267:
Still, I'm happy enough just seeing
him again.
